The paper deals with image classification using dictionary learning, which is a common technique in computer vision (CV) and machine learning (ML). Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also introduces a regularization term to improve the discriminative capability of representation coefficients, which falls under the category of ML algorithms and techniques, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of label information, which is a common theme in artificial intelligence (AI) research, making cs.AI a possible sub-category. The paper uses benchmark databases to evaluate the proposed method, which is a common practice in multimedia (MM) research, making cs.MM another possible sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with image classification, which is a common task in information retrieval (IR), making cs.IR a possible sub-category.
